<dl id="n35216a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35216a">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35216a"> 216(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cling to / Kaaba curtains</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<i>The Ceremonies and Merwa</i>.&mdash; [&hellip;]</font> the wild Bedouins of the Yemen mountains came in thousands to barter for their cattle and fruits for clothing <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font>. Though ignorant of the legal ritual and prayers, they performed the tawaf with enthusiasm, throwing themselves against the Ka&apos;ba and clinging to its curtains as a child clings to its mother. <small> &ldquo;MECCA&rdquo; <a name="EBMC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBMC"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 954</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
